Yulia Tymoshenko and her faction "Batkivshchyna" did not support the scandalous law on mobilization, which was just voted in the parliament. They categorically opposed, in particular, the fact that this law does not provide for the provision of demobilization of military personnel who have served in the army for more than 36 months.

Yulia Tymoshenko explained that the law, which has a maximum of unconstitutional coercion and repression, will not be able to create a strong army capable of repelling the enemy.
She and the Batkivshchyna team demanded the following amendments to the bill:
- immediate demobilization of all those who have served 36 months or more;
- establish clear deadlines for rotations and vacations;
- pay $10,000 to everyone who signs a contract with the Ministry of Defense;
- to double - up to 200,000 hryvnias - monetary support for every soldier who fights on the front line;
- train new recruits for at least 6 months before going to the front;
- remove from the law all repressive positions that are unconstitutional;
- give peace to students, graduate students, lecturers, teachers, educators, people with disabilities and those who care for them, as well as parents of large families;
- remove armor from officials and deputies, law enforcement officers and judges - everyone must be equal before the law;
- treat the wounded at state expense in medical facilities of any level and ownership;
- teach the children of fallen heroes at universities for free.

Not a single amendment to the law on mobilization was taken into account, and therefore the "Fatherland" faction did not support it in the session hall. Ukraine 24/7

